{"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc18\/407","type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (50 min)","isActive":true},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"All apps benefit from a focus on performance and an increase in overall responsiveness. This information packed session gives you strategies for fixing performance problems using Instruments and other tools. Additionally, get practical advice based on experience in tuning Apple’s own apps including Xcode and Photos on iOS."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All performance work should be based on measurement"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Make sure to improve performance on features used by all users instead of edge cases","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two tests to do:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unit tests:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Focused benchmarks"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolate issues"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Pinpoints regressions","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Integration Tests","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Measures user experience","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Measures dependencies"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Measures side effects","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the Time Profile"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On the bottom left, you have several filters, use them to best accommodate your necessities (to visualize just the things you care about)","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"WWDC18-407-separateThread","type":"image"}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"How fast your application has to be to be considered "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"instant"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":"?"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"Apple considers an app instant when it is ready to be used as soon as the zoom animation from the home screen (when you tap the icon) is completed. This takes between "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"500ms","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" to "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"600ms","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Be lazy, proactive, constant (regardless of the amount of data we need to load), and timely (no drop frames!)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Things to analyze\/do:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On launch:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Load database early","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Review the queries done during launch","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensure required queries are efficient as possible"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Evaluate if information is really needed during launch"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}]}]},{"content":[{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Storyboards:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensure only the visible views are loaded (I’m sooo guilty on this one)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Do as little work as possible in the initializers","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On the visible views","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Load only the needed data synchronously"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Schedule preheating of the remaining data asynchronously (on background threads)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cache information","type":"text"}]}]}]}]}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Written-By","text":"Written By"},{"numberOfColumns":5,"type":"row","columns":[{"size":1,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"zntfdr"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"size":4,"content":[{"text":"zntfdr","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"zntfdr"},{"inlineContent":[{"overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Contributed Notes"}],"isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Missing anything? Corrections? ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Related-Sessions","text":"Related Sessions"},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10142-Build-scalable-enterprise-app-suites","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-219-Image-and-Graphics-Best-Practices","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-403-Whats-New-in-Testing","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-405-Measuring-Performance-Using-Logging","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-417-Testing-Tips-and-Tricks","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-411-System-Trace-in-Depth","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-418-Using-Time-Profiler-in-Instruments","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC15-409-Optimizing-Swift-Performance"],"style":"list","type":"links"},{"type":"small","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Legal Notice"}]}]},{"type":"small","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All content copyright © 2012 – 2025 Apple Inc. All rights reserved."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Swift, the Swift logo, Swift Playgrounds, Xcode, Instruments, Cocoa Touch, Touch ID, FaceID, iPhone, iPad, Safari, Apple Vision, Apple Watch, App Store, iPadOS, watchOS, visionOS, tvOS, Mac, and macOS are trademarks of Apple Inc., registered in the U.S. and other countries."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This website is not made by, affiliated with, nor endorsed by Apple."}]}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-407-Practical-Approaches-to-Great-App-Performance"},"kind":"article","sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-407-practical-approaches-to-great-app-performance"]}],"metadata":{"title":"Practical Approaches to Great App Performance","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC18","role":"sampleCode"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"references":{"zntfdr":{"type":"image","identifier":"zntfdr","alt":"Profile image of zntfdr","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","images":[{"identifier":"WWDC18-Icon.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"WWDC18.jpeg","type":"card"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18","role":"collectionGroup","title":"WWDC18","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 10, Swift 4.2, iOS 12, macOS 10.14 (Mojave), tvOS 12, watchOS 5."}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-411-System-Trace-in-Depth":{"title":"System Trace in Depth","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-411-system-trace-in-depth","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-411-System-Trace-in-Depth","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Join engineers from the Instruments team for another focused look at the System Trace Instruments profiling template and how to get the most out of it. Discover how threads, virtual memory, and locking interact to affect performance. Dive deep for a practical look at how you can improve your app’s responsiveness and keep your users engaged."}],"type":"topic","kind":"article"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributions are welcome!","type":"text"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link","title":"Contributions are welcome!","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10142-Build-scalable-enterprise-app-suites":{"abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to build focused enterprise apps that work well together. In this session, we’ll introduce you to Apple Retail’s suite of enterprise apps, which help employees interact with customers, track operations, manage stores, and stay connected. Discover how Apple Retail created a unified set of apps by adopting Swift Packages and testing for app scalability. And explore how managing apps in production with configurations can help tailor app suites to different regions and locations.","type":"text"}],"role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10142-build-scalable-enterprise-app-suites","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Build scalable enterprise app suites","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10142-Build-scalable-enterprise-app-suites"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"WWDC18.jpeg":{"identifier":"WWDC18.jpeg","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-405-Measuring-Performance-Using-Logging":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-405-Measuring-Performance-Using-Logging","title":"Measuring Performance Using Logging","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-405-measuring-performance-using-logging","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to use signposts and logging to measure performance.  Understand how the Points of Interest instrument can be used to examine logged data. Get an introduction into creating and using custom instruments."}],"role":"sampleCode","type":"topic"},"https://":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/","url":"https:\/\/","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Blog"}],"title":"Blog"},"https://developer.apple.com/wwdc18/407":{"checksum":null,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc18\/407","type":"download","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc18\/407"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image"},"https://github.com/zntfdr":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GitHub"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr","type":"link","title":"GitHub","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC15-409-Optimizing-Swift-Performance":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC15-409-Optimizing-Swift-Performance","title":"Optimizing Swift Performance","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc15-409-optimizing-swift-performance","kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"Hear from the experts about how you can write faster Swift code and use Instruments to identify performance bottlenecks. Dive deep into specific techniques that will help you produce the most efficient code possible.","type":"text"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-403-Whats-New-in-Testing":{"role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"Hear about exciting improvements to code coverage, including how you can build your own automation on top of Xcode’s coverage reports. Learn how to dramatically speed up the execution of your tests by leveraging distributed parallel testing, new in Xcode 10.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-403-whats-new-in-testing","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-403-Whats-New-in-Testing","title":"What’s New in Testing"},"WWDC18-Icon.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC18-Icon.png","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-417-Testing-Tips-and-Tricks":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Testing is an essential tool to consistently verify your code works correctly, but often your code has dependencies that are out of your control. Discover techniques for making hard-to-test code testable on Apple platforms using XCTest. Learn a variety of tips for writing higher-quality tests that run fast and require less maintenance."}],"role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-417-testing-tips-and-tricks","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Testing Tips & Tricks","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-417-Testing-Tips-and-Tricks"},"WWDC18-407-separateThread":{"identifier":"WWDC18-407-separateThread","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-407-separateThread.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-418-Using-Time-Profiler-in-Instruments":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to make your apps faster and more efficient in this introduction to Time Profiler in Instruments. Walk through how to use Time Profiler to measure your app’s performance. Learn how Time Profiler works and can be used to identify problems and verify your fixes. Discover how easy it is to improve your app’s power usage and performance by using Instruments throughout your development process."}],"role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","title":"Using Time Profiler in Instruments","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-418-Using-Time-Profiler-in-Instruments","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-418-using-time-profiler-in-instruments"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-219-Image-and-Graphics-Best-Practices":{"title":"Image and Graphics Best Practices","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-219-Image-and-Graphics-Best-Practices","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-219-image-and-graphics-best-practices","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Whether it’s for UI elements or a fundamental part of your application, at some point, you have to handle images. This session is packed with engaging insight into how images are handled in iOS including discussion of UIImage, UIImageView, custom drawing in UIKit, plus advanced CPU and GPU techniques that can help you maximize performance and minimize memory footprint."}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/zntfdr":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","images":[{"identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg","type":"card"},{"identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg","type":"icon"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/zntfdr","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr","role":"sampleCode","title":"zntfdr (332 notes)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"No Bio on GitHub"}]},"zntfdr.jpeg":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg","type":"image","alt":null}}}